HEADWORD: Impone
<hw>Im*pone"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imponere</ets>, <ets>impositum</ets>, to place upon; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>ponere</ets> to place. See
<er>Position</er>.]</ety> <def>To stake; to wager; to pledge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Against the which he has <qex>imponed</qex>, as I take it, six
French rapiers and poniards.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

